data.title: Prince Christian of Schleswig-Holstein; Princess Helena Augusta Victoria of Schleswig-Holstein Greetings Card
data.meta_description: Send them something special with a greetings card printed to order from over 138,000 images from the National Portrait Gallery Collection
data.text:
Blank greetings card with envelope featuring:

Prince Christian of Schleswig-Holstein; Princess Helena Augusta Victoria of Schleswig-Holstein NPG Ax46735

© National Portrait Gallery, London

by John Jabez Edwin Mayall

Princess Helena Augusta Victoria of Schleswig-Holstein was a member of the British Royal Family, the fifth-born child and the third daughter of Queen Victoria. In 1866 she married Prince (Frederick) Christian of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg. Helena devoted much time and effort to charitable causes. She set up and helped to supervise a holiday house for deprived and handicapped London children near Cumberland Lodge, and she was a founder member of the Red Cross. She was active in voluntary work during the First World War. In... more
